Sentencas: Developing cathodes capable of working at intermediate temperatures (IT) is key to improving solid oxide fuel cells' (SOFC) durability, ease of operation, and manufacturing cost reduction.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: BaFeO3-delta (BFO)-based perovskites are ideal candidates because of their fast kinetics, which is due to the mixed conduction of oxygen vacancies and electron-holes.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Thus, maximizing their oxygen vacancy and hole concentration can further enhance oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) catalysis.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: This work proposes to achieve this by generating A-site deficiency, which introduces negative charges into the perovskite crystal.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The paper presents a computational and experimental analysis of this strategy on BFO-based cathodes, using (Ba0.95La0.05)(1-x)FeO3-delta as a case study.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: A-site deficiency increases the concentration of oxygen vacancies and holes, improving ORR catalysis.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: In addition, it eases oxygen surface exchange by hindering Ba segregation.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: As a result, A-site deficiency improves the overall electrochemical properties of BFO-based cathodes, providing a simple and effective method to enhance their performance.
Titulo: The influence of A-site deficiency on the electrochemical properties of (Ba0.95La0.05)1-xFeO3-δ as an intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode
